<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> THE AEGIS OF LIFE</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'><body>

<p><b><font size="4">The Aegis of Life</font></b></p>

<p><b>Chapter 1 : </b>Searching the lands, acquiring fame, fortune and
might, you wander the streets of Qeynos.  You are aware of a Lord Grimrot,
wandering the Plains of Karana, killing people and using great magics to
transform himself, you know he must be stopped and have gone into Qeynos to seek
more information.  You find yourself at the "UFO" and decide to
visit (Paladin).  He seems troubled when you find him.   You ask
him of Lord Grimrot and he begins...</p>
<p><b>Chapter 2 : </b>He tells you of Grimrot's evil deeds and how he must be
destroyed.  Lord Grimrot has two forms.  Even though you may kill his
human self, which has been done before, he comes back and wanders the land as a
skeleton!  You must destroy Grimrot in both of his forms and return his
decayed heart, and a scythe (NO DROP).  Once you return these items, the
people of Qeynos will gift you with a symbol of your Goodness!  The Aegeis
of Life shall be yours.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 3 : </b>You set out from Qeynos, the citizens granting you gifts
of flowers and food.  You wander a day and night through the Western Plains
and through the Northern Plains.  You finally reach the river and find the
great stone bridge that will bring you to the Southern Plains of Karana. 
Guards at the stone bridge tell you of Lord Grimrot and know he appears near
them every once in a while, casting magics on the Guards and scaring them to
death.  You cross the bridge and climb a hill to the west, watching the
lands, searching for Lord Grimrot.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 4 : </b>After what seems AGES, you notice Lord Grimrot lurking
along the shores, kneeling along the waters and fishing.  You approach Lord
Grimrot and draw your Blade.  Lord Grimrot stands, drops his pole and
unsheaths a great Scythe!  "A pity one such as thee shall fall to thy
doom!" And with that battle ensues!  A long and hardened fight, Lord
Grimrot finally falls to a blow that shatters his Scythe and kills him outright. 
You pull the Scythe from his deadened hands and sit down to nurse your wounds. 
A short time later you look to the shore and find that Lord Grimrot's corpse is
gone! </p>
<p><b>Chapter 5 : </b>You make camp for the night to rest up before continuing
your search.  Late that night, you hear a clicking in the darkness and
stand up, pulling your blade from its sheath.  You begin to smell a vile,
putrid stench.  As you peer into the trees, a skeleton, dressed in Lord
Grimrot's jacket slinks towards you.  You can see his heart, black and
shrunken, dripping a blackened juice that oozes his spirit and soul.  You
call upon the might of Marr and Ward his attacks, swinging Ghoulbane and bashing
with your Shield.  The skeleton puts up a good fight, but in the end, no
Undead can truly harm you!  You pull the skeletons heart out from its
broken ribcage and watch it disintegrate before your eyes.   You
stumble into the Guard Towers and sleep the rest of the night.</p>
<p><b>Chapter 6 : </b>The Guards make you a hearty breakfast in the morning and
set out for Qeynos the moment you are ready.  You arrive back in Qeynos and
news travelled fast ahead of you.  (Paladin) was waiting for your arrival. 
You hand him the Heart and Scythe of Lord Grimrot, triumphant and pleased. 
(Paladin) hands you a Golden Encrusted Shield, naming it the Aegeis of Life. 
You strap the Shield to your back and thank him profusely.  Wassail!</p>
<p><b>Notes : </b>The faction requirements for this Quest are right off the
maps.  Even at amiable faction, if you are not maxed out with faction, you
will have to find and kill Grimrot all over again.  There are a number of
ways to restore faction.  Here is Snowxan's comments and what he did to
gain the proper faction:</p>
<blockquote>
  <p><i>The only way I found you can get a reasonable amount of faction (and a
  nice percentage of loot, i made about 150pp in one run) is the bandit sash
  quest. I fill up 5 full backpacks about 12 times before my faction was amiable
  with the Temple of Life... and I THOUGHT that I could turn in the scythe and
  heart to the head paladin in Qeynos... I was WRONG! Then I had to go out and
  kill Grimrot again with a few friends of mine. This takes a LONG time to
  complete, but well worth it.</i></p>
</blockquote>
<p>The stats on the Aegeis of Life are as follows : </p>
<p>Aegeis of Life <br>
Magic item - Lore Item - NO DROP<br>
Charges:1 (superior healing) AC:12- Wis +10- Sv Dis +25<br>
Classes: CLR, PAL<br>
Races: HUM, BAR, ERU, ELF, HIE, DEF, HEF, DWF, HFL, GNM</p>

